word_mean_info__list.difference: 通常指表面上的坑或凹处，也指物体内部的空洞。
比hole正式，指实体内中或表面的空洞或空腔。
指天然的大洞，尤指地上的洞，也指为采掘矿物而挖的深洞。

弹孔；爆破孔；炮眼；穿孔；蛀洞

bilingual.source: Each time a new air hole was made, the work crews cheered and commenced work on the next one.
bilingual.target: 每次一个新的通气孔被打通，工人们就欢呼并开始下一个的工作。

bilingual.source: Then, one day, as Samuel and Irniq stood beside an air hole they watched a rising shadow through the ice.
bilingual.target: 然后，有一天，当塞缪尔和伊尔尼克站在一个通气孔旁时，他们看到冰下有一个上升的影子。

bilingual.source: The design drawing indicates the pitch-row of each hole.
bilingual.target: 设计图上标明了每个孔的孔距。

bilingual.source: The pin was carefully inserted into the hole.
bilingual.target: 这个销钉很小心地插入了孔中。

bilingual.source: Use an expander to increase the size of the hole.
bilingual.target: 使用扩展器来增大孔的尺寸。

bilingual.source: Insert the coak into the hole to secure the parts.
bilingual.target: 将插销插入孔中以固定部件。

bilingual.source: The countersunk hole allows the screw to sit flush.
bilingual.target: 沉头的孔使螺钉可以平齐地嵌入。

bilingual.source: Use a reamer to enlarge the hole.
She drilled a small hole for the screw.
bilingual.target: 她为螺丝钻孔了一个小洞。

list.abstract: HOLE是洛杉矶的一支摇滚乐队，乐队成员有Erlandson，Love，Jill Emery，Caroline Rue。
《Hole》是王宇波演唱的歌曲，收录于《暴裂无声 电影原声带》专辑中，于2018年4月9日发行。

yingyinNormal.en: Why? I just want to check something. Okay. Now we'll see. Air hole. Air hole.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么？我只是想看一下。好，等着瞧吧。气孔！气孔。

yingyinNormal.en: Because of the black hole?
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为黑洞吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I fell down a hole and hit my head.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我掉进了一个洞里，撞到头了。

yingyinNormal.en: She fell down, down, down, deep in a hole.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她一直往下掉呀掉，掉到一个洞里了。

yingyinNormal.en: I've just had my dinner down a rabbit hole.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我刚在瑞贝卡家里吃过晚餐了。

yingyinNormal.en: There's a hole in the boat? It's full of holes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 船是不是有个洞？到处都是洞。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: You're in a hole, Ms. Walsh, best to stop digging.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你陷入泥沼了，沃尔什女士，别挣扎了。

yingyinNormal.en: The Wormhole is a three-dimensional hole in space.
yingyinNormal.zh: 虫洞是空间里的三维洞。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want to hear anymore about that guy's hole!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我一点都不想再听到那家伙的"洞"！

yingyinNormal.en: Which college? Ed's Learning Hole. Really? No! I am donezo.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哪所大学？艾德的学习之洞。真的吗？不是！我完了。

yingyinNormal.en: Around the water hole. The water hole? What's so great about the water hole?
yingyinNormal.zh: 就在水洞附近，水洞附近有什么了不起的啊？

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, an ass, A-hole. Yeah, an ass A-hole, all the way. You are a piece of work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 知道，把你看成混蛋。是啊，把我看成混蛋，肯定是的，你还真不简单啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, when you down in a hole, it looks like failure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当你身处困境时，这只是看似一种失败而已。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't leave it! You gouged a hole in my dingy floor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么能不管，你在我的旧地板上撬了个洞。

yingyinNormal.en: It is a rainy day and the school roof has a hole in it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天是个雨天，学校的屋顶上出现了一个洞。

yingyinNormal.en: He's making a funny face. I think I'll put a hole in it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他脸上的表情好滑稽。我给它开个洞吧。

yingyinNormal.en: That's a rabbit hole. We have to address it sooner or later.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那可是兔子洞啊(出自爱丽丝梦游仙境)。我们早晚得说这件事。

yingyinNormal.en: Mummy, would you cut a hole in this box for me? What for? You'll see. Mummy pig is cutting a hole in the cardboard box. There you are, Peppa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 妈妈，你能帮我在这个箱子上剪个洞吗？要干什么？你会知道的。猪妈妈正在纸箱子上剪洞。好了，佩佩。

yingyinNormal.en: Brick, please. First, Daddy Pig fills the hole with bricks. There.
yingyinNormal.zh: 麻烦给我块砖。首先，爸爸要用砖堵上大洞。好了。

yingyinNormal.en: Brick, please. First, Daddy Pig fills the hole with bricks. There.
yingyinNormal.zh: 麻烦给我块砖。首先，爸爸要用砖堵上大洞。好了。

数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: The sand under the hill defeated several attempts by Higgins' workers to make a proper <highlight>hole</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Higgins的工人们多次试图挖一个合适的洞，但都被山下的沙子打败了。

examination_example.sentence: What prevented Higgins' workers from digging a proper <highlight>hole</highlight> to get the oil?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 是什么阻止了希金斯的工人挖一个合适的洞来获取石油？

examination_example.sentence: Architects have identified three main <highlight>holes</highlight> in the structure, in the locations of the spire, the main hall.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 建筑师已经确定了结构上的三个主要洞，在塔尖的位置，也就是主厅。

examination_example.sentence: One day after watching a science program, a little boy decided to dig a <highlight>hole</highlight> behind his house.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一天，在看完一个科学节目后，一个小男孩决定在他的房子后面挖一个洞。

examination_example.sentence: Then they found out there was a <highlight>hole</highlight> in the floor of the boat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后他们发现船的地板上有一个洞。

examination_example.sentence: Make a <highlight>hole</highlight> under your car and lie there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在你的车底挖一个洞，躺在那里。
